Monsoon rains and snowmelt have left 200,000 people stranded in northern Bangladesh, exacerbating the country's annual flooding crisis.
The Brahmaputra river is overflowing, posing a significant threat.
The death toll in India, Bangladesh, and Nepal has surpassed 100, with millions displaced.
The government is mobilizing resources to aid those affected, with relief efforts underway.
The situation is dire, with millions marooned and homes destroyed.
International aid, including 2.5 million USD from the UK, is being directed towards providing essential supplies and support to those impacted by the devastating floods in Bangladesh.
